  this.editMode = this.editMode ? false : true; 
}
```
And in your template:
```
&lt;button  (click)=&quot;toggleEditMode()&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-secondary&quot;&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;far fa-edit&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/button&gt;
```

If you want to open one edit at a time, you need to have an unique identifier for each item. You can do it with the help of a boolean variable and the index of the iteration in template. Here is a simplified example of your code, where we use the variable `editMode` that you have, but let&#39;s attach the index too:

&lt;!-- language-all: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;table&gt;
    	&lt;tr&gt;
    		&lt;th&gt;Product&lt;/th&gt;
    		&lt;th&gt;Category&lt;/th&gt;
        &lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
    	&lt;/tr&gt;
    	&lt;tr *ngFor=&quot;let item of items; index as i&quot;&gt;
    		&lt;ng-container *ngIf=&quot;editMode !== i&quot;&gt;
    			&lt;td&gt;{{item.productName}}&lt;/td&gt;
    			&lt;td&gt;{{item.categoryName}}&lt;/td&gt;
    		&lt;/ng-container&gt;
            &lt;! -- if assigned index to editMode matches --&gt;
    		&lt;ng-container *ngIf=&quot;editMode === i&quot;&gt;
    			&lt;td&gt;&lt;input [(ngModel)]=&quot;item.productName&quot; /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    			&lt;td&gt;&lt;input [(ngModel)]=&quot;item.categoryName&quot; /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    		&lt;/ng-container&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;
          &lt;!-- Assign the index to edit mode, which item clicked --&gt;
          &lt;button (click)=&quot;editMode = i&quot;&gt;Edit&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/td&gt;
    	&lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;

And when you have done the edit, just set `editMode` to `false`.

